{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Pdnpmk3sQEPUrRgmY88RWe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the exact problem confirmed:\n\n```\nmaster not discovered yet, this node has not previously joined a bootstrapped (v7+) cluster, and [cluster.initial_master_nodes] is empty on this node\n```\n\nAll 3 nodes have discovered each other (es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2 are all visible), but `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is empty, so no node knows which nodes are eligible to be the initial master.\n\nThe fix:\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap with all 3 node names\n2. Restart the ES pods (delete them so they get recreated by the StatefulSet) to pick up the new config\n3. Wait for the cluster to form and elect a master, then remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap since it's only needed for initial bootstrap and should be stripped out afterward to avoid re-bootstrap issues if quorum is lost\n4. Do a rolling restart of the pods one by one to verify stability\n\nLet me write the fix by updating the ConfigMap with the initial master nodes setting.\n\nWriting Elasticsearch config...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":853,"cache_read_input_tokens":36904,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":853},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e492bcc8-ef20-4b02-8295-c07e351b5d93","uuid":"3df77b50-dd54-48ca-a1ad-85c1c9e5398a","request_id":"req_011CcQ2D8JY9KwoyGJ5vAXtz"}
