{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CiaNq1KS52THGAF1yZr4pH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals achieved. Here's a summary of what was done and why each step matters:\n\n---\n\n**Root cause:** The ConfigMap `es-config` was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. In Elasticsearch 7.x, a fresh cluster cannot elect its first master without this setting — every node sees the others via `discovery.seed_hosts` but none knows which are eligible to bootstrap the cluster, producing \"master not discovered yet\".\n\n**Fix applied (3 stages):**\n\n1. **Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]`** to the ConfigMap, then restarted all pods. The cluster bootstrapped and elected es-cluster-0 as master (status: green, 3 nodes).\n\n2. **Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap.** This setting is bootstrap-only — keeping it after cluster formation is dangerous because it can trigger accidental re-bootstrapping if quorum is temporarily lost. After first formation, the cluster persists master knowledge in its on-disk state, so the setting is no longer needed.\n\n3. **Rolling restart (one pod at a time).** Each pod reloaded the trimmed config. The cluster stayed green throughout — confirming `discovery.seed_hosts` alone is sufficient for all future restarts.\n\n**Final state:**\n- Status: **green**, 3 nodes, 3 data nodes, master = es-cluster-0\n- ConfigMap has no `cluster.initial_master_nodes` — safe for all future restarts"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":769,"cache_read_input_tokens":42512,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":769},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e492bcc8-ef20-4b02-8295-c07e351b5d93","u